str2: To go forward, go on, advance; I go before, precede. From pro and erchomai; to go onward, precede.
Little, small. Including the comparative mikroteros apparently a primary word; small (figuratively) dignity).

str2: A reduplicated and contracted form of peto; probably akin to petomai through the idea of alighting; to fall.
From pros and ops; the front, i.e. The countenance, aspect, appearance, surface; by implication, presence, person.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To pray, pray for, offer prayer. From pros and euchomai; to pray to God, i.e. Supplicate, worship.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 1st Person Singular
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
Father, (Heavenly) Father, ancestor, elder, senior. Apparently a primary word; a 'father'.
If. A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
(a) of persons: powerful, able, (b) of things: possible. From dunamai; powerful or capable; neuter possible.
This; he, she, it.
A drinking cup, the contents of the cup; fig: the portion which God allots.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From para and erchomai; to come near or aside, i.e. To approach, go by, perish or neglect, avert.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.

str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
However, nevertheless, but, except that, yet. From pleion; moreover, i.e. Albeit, save that, rather, yet.
No, not. Also ouk, and ouch a primary word; the absolute negative adverb; no or not.
Probably adverb of comparative from hos; which how, i.e. In that manner.
